flowRoot.flowPara: One mans infrastructure is another mans stapler. Depending on what you're doing, anything can be infrastructure and anything can be extrastructure. By "critical infrastructure" we mean infrastructure which is required as an absolute baseline for a surviving society. Not necessarily a thriving one. First you survive, then you make life pleasant.

Varied definitions exist. Wikipedia says: "Infrastructure is the basic physical and organizational structures needed for the operation of a society or enterprise, or the services and facilities necessary for
an economy to function." This is
more in terms of quality of
infrastructures that may help guide you in the completion of worksheet 1. To the left is an example circular infrastructure map.
